<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why must you hate me only because i am still there and killin?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm not in IV.  I've never even played on Kane Bayle.  For that matter, I barely even play everquest anymore, I haven't really in months.  What I'm referring to is what I've heard from multiple members of your own guild who say that officers and their twinks take all the loot and that you ebay, and that you have a habit of banning anyone that dares to question you on the boards.<br>
<br>
I don't buy your arguments for God loot.  Points distribute loot far more fairly, if you're using God loot, it's just a way of whoring power.  It's undemocratic by its very nature.  Why should a group of a few members of your guild have the right to determine who gets loot for the rest of the guild?  Maybe if people felt they had some influence and that their opinions mattered, they'd play more and your turnover wouldn't be so insanely high.  People aren't happy getting officer scraps.<br>
<br>
I actually did God loot for a while when I was running Promethian Order, I know what it's all about and how it works, and I moved the guild to DKP, reducing my own power dramatically, but giving every member a say in his own destiny.  Our turnout went through the roof after we switched.  (Note: I'm not now in Promethian Order, nor have I been for some time.  I don't actively play everquest anymore.)<br>
<br>
If God loot guilds really wanted to be democratic, but had a genuine belief that God loot was superior, then why not rotate the council of people who award loot through all members of the guild?  That would give everyone a say at least.<br>
<br>
